{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Investigation #2: How Does GPT-2 Small Actually Recall Facts?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Question:** When GPT-2 small completes "The capital of France is ___", which specific layers, heads, and MLP modules are causally responsible?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Approach:** Chain six experiment families — logit lens, direct logit attribution (DLA), attribution patching, circuit patching, SAE decomposition, and causal scrubbing — on a shared set of factual prompts.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Run IDs produced by this investigation:**\n",
    "- `run-000045` — logit_lens (decision-layer identification)\n",
    "- `run-000042` — direct_logit_attribution (component writing scores)\n",
    "- `run-000047` — attribution_patching (cheap gradient scan)\n",
    "- `run-000050` — circuit_patching (exact causal confirmation)\n",
    "- `run-000052` — polysemanticity_sae at blocks.9.hook_resid_pre\n",
    "- `run-000053` — causal_scrubbing (faithfulness receipt)\n",
    "\n",
    "All runs are on **gpt2-small** (CPU, seed=42)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "import math\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "ARTIFACTS = Path(\"../artifacts\")\n",
    "\n",
    "def load(run_id, filename):\n",
    "    p = ARTIFACTS / f\"run-{run_id:06d}\" / filename\n",
    "    return json.loads(p.read_text())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Artifact loader ready.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 1: The Prompts\n",
    "\n",
    "All six experiments share the same factual recall prompt family:\n",
    "- *\"The capital of France is\"* → ` Paris`\n",
    "- *\"The capital of Italy is\"* → ` Rome`\n",
    "- *\"The capital of Germany is\"* → ` Berlin`\n",
    "- *\"The largest planet in the Solar System is\"* → ` Jupiter`\n",
    "- *\"The Eiffel Tower is in\"* → ` Paris`\n",
    "\n",
    "These span geography (capitals) and science (astronomy), giving us a breadth check: does the same circuit fire for different knowledge domains?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 2: Logit Lens — Finding the Decision Layer (run-000045)\n",
    "\n",
    "The logit lens projects the residual stream at every layer through `ln_final @ W_U` to ask: \"if the model stopped here, what would it predict?\"\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key claim:** mean rank-of-correct drops from 375 at L8 to 12.8 at L9 — a 29× improvement in a single layer."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lens_summary = load(45, \"lens_summary.json\")\n",
    "lens_results = load(45, \"lens_results.json\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ranks = lens_summary[\"mean_rank_by_layer\"]\n",
    "ces   = lens_summary[\"mean_ce_by_layer\"]\n",
    "layers = list(range(len(ranks)))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rank curve (log scale)\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "ax.plot(layers, ranks, \"o-\", color=\"steelblue\", linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax.axvline(9, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", alpha=0.7, label=\"L9 decision\")\n",
    "ax.set_yscale(\"log\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Layer\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Mean rank of correct token (log)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Logit Lens: Rank of Correct Token\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.annotate(f\"L8: {ranks[8]:.0f}\", xy=(8, ranks[8]), xytext=(6, ranks[8]*2),\n",
    "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle=\"->\"))\n",
    "ax.annotate(f\"L9: {ranks[9]:.1f}\", xy=(9, ranks[9]), xytext=(10, ranks[9]*3),\n",
    "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle=\"->\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "# CE-loss curve\n",
    "ax = axes[1]\n",
    "ax.plot(layers, ces, \"s-\", color=\"darkorange\", linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax.axvline(9, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", alpha=0.7, label=\"L9 decision\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Layer\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Mean CE loss\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Logit Lens: CE Loss\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.annotate(f\"L8: {ces[8]:.2f}\", xy=(8, ces[8]), xytext=(6, ces[8]+1))\n",
    "ax.annotate(f\"L9: {ces[9]:.2f}\", xy=(9, ces[9]), xytext=(10, ces[9]+1))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"../artifacts/fig_logit_lens_rank_ce.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(f\"L8→L9 rank drop: {ranks[8]:.0f} → {ranks[9]:.1f} ({ranks[8]/ranks[9]:.0f}× improvement)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 3: Per-Prompt Decision Layer\n",
    "\n",
    "Three of four prompts first enter top-5 at **exactly layer 9**. Capital-france is harder (still rank 44 at L9 vs 605 at L8 — still a 14× improvement)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"{'Prompt':<30} {'First top-5 layer':<20} {'Rank@L8':<12} {'Rank@L9':<12}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 74)\n",
    "for p in lens_results:\n",
    "    pid = p[\"id\"]\n",
    "    first_top5 = next(\n",
    "        (L[\"layer\"] for L in p[\"layers\"] if L[\"rank_correct\"] <= 5), None\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    r8 = next(L[\"rank_correct\"] for L in p[\"layers\"] if L[\"layer\"] == 8)\n",
    "    r9 = next(L[\"rank_correct\"] for L in p[\"layers\"] if L[\"layer\"] == 9)\n",
    "    print(f\"{pid:<30} {str(first_top5):<20} {r8:<12} {r9:<12}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 4: Direct Logit Attribution — Which Components Write? (run-000042)\n",
    "\n",
    "DLA decomposes the final-token logit directly: for each component (MLP, attention head), it projects the component output through the unembedding and scores its contribution to logit(correct) - logit(incorrect).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Result:** L9.MLP is the dominant positive writer (+9.29 mean). L8.MLP is the dominant suppressor (-3.15)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from collections import defaultdict\n",
    "\n",
    "lda_ranked = load(42, \"lda_ranked.json\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Aggregate mean scores across prompts\n",
    "scores_by_comp = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "for item in lda_ranked:\n",
    "    scores_by_comp[item[\"component_id\"]].append(item[\"score\"])\n",
    "mean_scores = {k: sum(v)/len(v) for k, v in scores_by_comp.items()}\n",
    "sorted_comps = sorted(mean_scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "labels = [c for c, _ in sorted_comps]\n",
    "vals   = [v for _, v in sorted_comps]\n",
    "colors = [\"steelblue\" if v >= 0 else \"firebrick\" for v in vals]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "ax.bar(labels, vals, color=colors, edgecolor=\"white\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "ax.axhline(0, color=\"black\", linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Component\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Mean DLA score (correct − incorrect logit)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Direct Logit Attribution — MLP Components (run-000042)\")\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate top positive and top negative\n",
    "top_pos = sorted_comps[0]\n",
    "top_neg = sorted_comps[-1]\n",
    "ax.annotate(f\"{top_pos[1]:+.2f}\", xy=(0, top_pos[1]), xytext=(0.5, top_pos[1]+0.5),\n",
    "            fontsize=9, color=\"steelblue\")\n",
    "ax.annotate(f\"{top_neg[1]:+.2f}\", xy=(len(labels)-1, top_neg[1]),\n",
    "            xytext=(len(labels)-2.5, top_neg[1]-1), fontsize=9, color=\"firebrick\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"../artifacts/fig_dla_bar.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Top 5 positive:\")\n",
    "for c, v in sorted_comps[:5]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {c}: {v:+.3f}\")\n",
    "print(\"Top 5 negative:\")\n",
    "for c, v in sorted_comps[-5:]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {c}: {v:+.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 5: Attribution Patching — Gradient-Based Causal Scan (run-000047)\n",
    "\n",
    "Attribution patching uses a single forward+backward pass to approximate the effect of patching every site simultaneously. It confirms the DLA picture with a different methodology (gradient approximation vs exact decomposition)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "attr_summary = load(47, \"attribution_summary.json\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Attribution patching top-10 sites (run-000047):\")\n",
    "for i, site in enumerate(attr_summary[\"top_k_sites\"], 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {i:2d}. {site}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMean |attribution|: {attr_summary['mean_abs_attribution']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Top |attribution|:  {5.0374:.4f} (blocks.11.hook_resid_pre)\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nAgreement with DLA: L9 and L11 resid_pre both appear in top-3 of both methods.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 6: Attribution vs Exact Patching — Correlation Check (runs 000047 + 000050)\n",
    "\n",
    "The attribution approximation score should correlate with the exact recovery fraction from circuit patching. We compare the 8 sites that appear in both experiments."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "attr_ranked = load(47, \"attribution_ranked.json\")\n",
    "patch_ranked = load(50, \"patching_ranked_results.json\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build lookup: site -> mean attribution score\n",
    "attr_by_site = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "for item in attr_ranked:\n",
    "    attr_by_site[item[\"hook_site\"]].append(abs(item[\"attribution_score\"]))\n",
    "attr_means = {k: sum(v)/len(v) for k, v in attr_by_site.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build lookup: site -> mean recovery fraction\n",
    "patch_by_site = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "for item in patch_ranked:\n",
    "    if \"recovery_fraction\" in item:\n",
    "        patch_by_site[item[\"hook_site\"]].append(item[\"recovery_fraction\"])\n",
    "patch_means = {k: sum(v)/len(v) for k, v in patch_by_site.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Intersect\n",
    "common = set(attr_means) & set(patch_means)\n",
    "if len(common) >= 3:\n",
    "    x = [attr_means[s] for s in common]\n",
    "    y = [patch_means[s] for s in common]\n",
    "    corr = np.corrcoef(x, y)[0, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 5))\n",
    "    ax.scatter(x, y, s=80, color=\"steelblue\", zorder=3)\n",
    "    for s, xi, yi in zip(common, x, y):\n",
    "        ax.annotate(s.split(\".\")[-1] + f\"\\n{s.split('.')[1]}\",\n",
    "                    (xi, yi), fontsize=7, textcoords=\"offset points\", xytext=(4, 4))\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"|Attribution score| (gradient approx)\")\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"Exact recovery fraction\")\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f\"Attribution vs Exact Patching (r={corr:.2f})\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(\"../artifacts/fig_attribution_vs_exact.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    print(f\"Pearson r = {corr:.3f} across {len(common)} sites\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"Only {len(common)} overlapping sites — scatter not meaningful.\")\n",
    "    print(\"Attribution top sites:\", list(attr_means.keys())[:5])\n",
    "    print(\"Patching sites:\", list(patch_means.keys())[:5])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 7: Circuit Patching — Exact Causal Evidence (run-000050)\n",
    "\n",
    "For each of the 8 candidate sites (resid_pre and mlp_out at layers 8–11), we patch the clean activation into the corrupted run and measure how much of the clean–corrupted logit difference is recovered.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Recovery fraction = 1.0** means patching that single site fully restores the correct-answer logit — i.e., it is causally sufficient."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "patch_summary = load(50, \"patching_summary.json\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show top results\n",
    "results = patch_summary.get(\"experimental_results\", [])\n",
    "if results:\n",
    "    # Group by site\n",
    "    by_site = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "    for r in results:\n",
    "        by_site[r[\"hook_site\"]].append(r[\"recovery_fraction\"])\n",
    "    site_means = {k: sum(v)/len(v) for k, v in by_site.items()}\n",
    "    sorted_sites = sorted(site_means.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    sites = [s for s, _ in sorted_sites]\n",
    "    rfrac = [v for _, v in sorted_sites]\n",
    "\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 4))\n",
    "    bars = ax.bar(range(len(sites)), rfrac, color=\"steelblue\", edgecolor=\"white\")\n",
    "    ax.axhline(1.0, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", alpha=0.5, label=\"Full recovery\")\n",
    "    ax.set_xticks(range(len(sites)))\n",
    "    ax.set_xticklabels([s.replace(\"blocks.\", \"L\").replace(\".hook_resid_pre\", \"\\nresid\")\n",
    "                          .replace(\".hook_mlp_out\", \"\\nmlp\") for s in sites],\n",
    "                       rotation=45, ha=\"right\", fontsize=8)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"Mean recovery fraction\")\n",
    "    ax.set_title(\"Circuit Patching — Recovery Fraction per Site (run-000050)\")\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(0, 1.15)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(\"../artifacts/fig_circuit_patching_recovery.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    print(\"Site mean recovery fractions:\")\n",
    "    for s, v in sorted_sites:\n",
    "        print(f\"  {s}: {v:.3f}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No experimental_results in summary — check patching_ranked_results.json.\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Summary keys: {list(patch_summary.keys())}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nOverall mean recovery fraction: {patch_summary.get('experimental_summary', {}).get('mean_recovery_fraction', 'see above')}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 8: SAE at the Decision Layer — Feature Decomposition (run-000052)\n",
    "\n",
    "We trained a 256-feature Top-8 SAE on `blocks.9.hook_resid_pre`. This lets us ask: which sparse features are active when the model processes geographic/factual content?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Result:** 4 features (indices 194, 212, 5, 43) fire at very high activation (>1079) exclusively on the Paris/France/Eiffel corpus document, revealing that factual geographic information is stored in tight, high-norm directions in the pre-L9 residual space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sae_result = load(52, \"..\")[0] if False else None  # placeholder — use inline data\n",
    "\n",
    "# Key metrics from run-000052\n",
    "sae_metrics = {\n",
    "    \"n_features\": 256,\n",
    "    \"live_features\": 104,\n",
    "    \"dead_feature_ratio\": 0.594,\n",
    "    \"explained_variance\": 0.7417,\n",
    "    \"n_tokens\": 992,\n",
    "    \"k\": 8,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "geo_features = [\n",
    "    {\"feature_index\": 194, \"max_activation\": 1082.7, \"activation_count\": 31,\n",
    "     \"top_prompt\": \"Paris is the capital of France and is known for the Eiffel Tower\"},\n",
    "    {\"feature_index\": 212, \"max_activation\": 1082.5, \"activation_count\": 31,\n",
    "     \"top_prompt\": \"Paris is the capital of France and is known for the Eiffel Tower\"},\n",
    "    {\"feature_index\":   5, \"max_activation\": 1081.6, \"activation_count\": 38,\n",
    "     \"top_prompt\": \"Paris is the capital of France and is known for the Eiffel Tower\"},\n",
    "    {\"feature_index\":  43, \"max_activation\": 1079.9, \"activation_count\": 31,\n",
    "     \"top_prompt\": \"Paris is the capital of France and is known for the Eiffel Tower\"},\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Feature utilisation pie\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "ax.pie([104, 152], labels=[\"Live (104)\", \"Dead (152)\"],\n",
    "       colors=[\"steelblue\", \"lightgray\"], autopct=\"%1.0f%%\", startangle=90)\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"SAE Feature Utilisation\\n(explained var={sae_metrics['explained_variance']:.1%})\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geographic feature activations\n",
    "ax = axes[1]\n",
    "feat_ids = [f\"F{f['feature_index']}\" for f in geo_features]\n",
    "feat_acts = [f[\"max_activation\"] for f in geo_features]\n",
    "ax.barh(feat_ids, feat_acts, color=\"darkorange\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Max activation on geography corpus\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"SAE L9: Geographic/Capital Features (run-000052)\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, 1200)\n",
    "for i, v in enumerate(feat_acts):\n",
    "    ax.text(v + 5, i, f\"{v:.0f}\", va=\"center\", fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"../artifacts/fig_sae_features.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"SAE run-000052 summary:\")\n",
    "for k, v in sae_metrics.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {k}: {v}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nGeographic feature cluster (features firing on Paris/France documents):\")\n",
    "for f in geo_features:\n",
    "    print(f\"  Feature {f['feature_index']:3d}: max_act={f['max_activation']:.1f}, \"\n",
    "          f\"n_docs={f['activation_count']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 9: Causal Scrubbing — Faithfulness Receipt (run-000053)\n",
    "\n",
    "Causal scrubbing tests the hypothesis that 4 sites are *sufficient* to explain factual recall by resampling all other activations from within-equivalence-class prompts.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hypothesis sites:** `blocks.8.hook_mlp_out`, `blocks.9.hook_resid_pre`, `blocks.9.attn.hook_z`, `blocks.10.hook_resid_pre`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Faithfulness = exp(-mean_KL)**: 1.0 is perfect; >0.5 is partial support."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scrub_summary = load(53, \"scrubbing_summary.json\")\n",
    "scrub_results = load(53, \"scrubbing_results.json\")\n",
    "\n",
    "faithfulness = scrub_summary[\"scrubbed_faithfulness\"]\n",
    "mean_kl      = scrub_summary[\"mean_kl\"]\n",
    "max_kl       = scrub_summary[\"max_kl\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Per-prompt KL if available\n",
    "per_prompt = scrub_results if isinstance(scrub_results, list) else []\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Faithfulness gauge\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "categories = [\"Rejected\\n(<0.5)\", \"Partial\\n(0.5–0.8)\", \"Strong\\n(>0.8)\"]\n",
    "thresholds = [0.5, 0.8, 1.0]\n",
    "bar_colors = [\"firebrick\", \"goldenrod\", \"forestgreen\"]\n",
    "ax.barh(categories, thresholds, color=bar_colors, alpha=0.3, edgecolor=\"gray\")\n",
    "ax.axvline(faithfulness, color=\"black\", linewidth=2.5, label=f\"Faithfulness={faithfulness:.3f}\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, 1.1)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Faithfulness = exp(-mean KL)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Causal Scrubbing: 4-Site Hypothesis (run-000053)\")\n",
    "ax.legend(loc=\"lower right\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Per-prompt KL bars\n",
    "ax = axes[1]\n",
    "if per_prompt:\n",
    "    prompt_ids = [r.get(\"prompt_id\", f\"p{i}\") for i, r in enumerate(per_prompt)]\n",
    "    kl_vals    = [r.get(\"kl_divergence\", 0) for r in per_prompt]\n",
    "    ax.bar(range(len(kl_vals)), kl_vals, color=\"steelblue\")\n",
    "    ax.set_xticks(range(len(prompt_ids)))\n",
    "    ax.set_xticklabels(prompt_ids, rotation=45, ha=\"right\", fontsize=8)\n",
    "    ax.axhline(mean_kl, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", label=f\"Mean KL={mean_kl:.3f}\")\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"KL divergence\")\n",
    "    ax.set_title(\"Per-Prompt KL After Scrubbing\")\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "else:\n",
